# Changelog after meaningful changes

When you **complete** work that users will notice (UI, features, fixes, perf, copy, mobile, auth, API behavior), **add a release note** before ending the task.

## How

From repo root, with the **dev server and MySQL running** and **`CHANGELOG_INGEST_SECRET` set in `.env`**:

```bash
npm run changelog:add -- --title "Short headline" --summary "One or two sentences on what changed and why it matters." [--area "Section"]
```

- Use **`--entryKey`**: stable slug (e.g. `feature-name-2026-02`) when you might retry, so duplicates fail cleanly.
- **`--area`**: optional — e.g. `Deck builder`, `Collection`, `General`, `Auth`.

If the command fails (server down, missing secret), tell the user to run it after restart or set `CHANGELOG_INGEST_SECRET`. Do not skip documenting the change in your reply.

## Skip the changelog for

- Typos / comments-only / internal refactors with **no** user-visible effect  
- Dependency bumps with no behavior change (unless security-relevant to users)  
- Formatting-only diffs  

## Prod

Do **not** commit secrets. For production rows, operators use the same CLI with **`MTG_API_URL`** and Railway’s secret (see `docs/deployment-runbook.md`).
